"title": "7767: priests, institution in OT times",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7767: priests, institution in ot times",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Priests played an important role in the OT and were regarded as having a special status and place in the life of Israel.</p>\n<h2>Pagan priests in the OT</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:1-1Sam6:2\">1SA 6:1–6:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:5\">2KI 23:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:5\">HOS 10:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:4\">ZEP 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>The special status of priests</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:5\">EZR 1:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:2\">ISA 24:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:9\">HOS 4:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:11\">MIC 3:11</a></p>\n<h2>Associated with the descendants of Levi through Aaron</h2>\n<h3>The exclusive nature of the priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:49\">1CH 6:49</a></strong> <em>Only God has the right to nominate those who mediate between him and humanity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:16-Exod6:20\">EXO 6:16–6:20</a> <em>This genealogy shows Moses and Aaron were both descended from Levi</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:1\">EXO 28:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:44\">EXO 29:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:30\">EXO 30:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:40\">NUM 16:40</a>DEU <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:1\">18:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:21\">JER 33:21</a></p>\n<h3>Micah's priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:13\">JDG 17:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The Shiloh priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:3\">1CH 24:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:27\">1CH 6:27</a></p>\n<h3>The priests in Dan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:30\">JDG 18:30</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Descendants of Zadok</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:15-Ezek44:16\">EZK 44:15–44:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:17\">2SA 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:50-1Chr6:53\">1CH 6:50–6:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr24:3\">1CH 24:3</a></p>\n<h2>Criticism of priestly appointments that were not Levitical</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:31\">1KI 12:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:33\">1KI 13:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:13-2Chr11:14\">2CH 11:13–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:9\">2CH 13:9</a></p>\n<h2>The appointment of priests</h2>\n<h3>Their preliminary purification</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:4\">EXO 29:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:19\">EXO 30:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:12\">EXO 40:12</a></p>\n<h3>Their anointing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:30-Exod30:32\">EXO 30:30–30:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:3\">NUM 3:3</a> <em>Kings and priests also were anointed.</em></p>\n<h3>Their consecration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1\">EXO 29:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:12-Exod29:14\">EXO 29:12–29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:18\">EXO 29:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:20-Exod29:21\">EXO 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a></p>\n<h3>Their ordination</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:35\">EXO 29:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:29\">EXO 29:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:33\">EXO 29:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:22\">LEV 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:33\">LEV 8:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:5\">JDG 17:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:12\">JDG 17:12</a></p>\n<h2>The dress of the priests</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:40\">EXO 28:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:42\">EXO 28:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:27-Exod39:29\">EXO 39:27–39:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:13\">LEV 8:13</a></p>",
